                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/symfony2-rest/edit/master/knpu/episode1/tests-clear-data.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>Using a random nickname in a test is weird: we should be explicit about our
input and output. Just set it to <code>ObjectOrienter</code>. Now it's easy to make our
asserts more specific, like for the <code>Location</code> header using <code>assertEquals</code>,
which should be <code>/api/programmers/ObjectOrienter</code>. And now use the method
<code>getHeader()</code>:</p>
